
To create a web-based personal finance tracker using JavaScript, HTML, and CSS, follow these general steps:

Start by setting up the project directory and files, including the index.html page, style sheet (style.css), and script file (script.js).

Design the layout of the pages using HTML elements, such as headers, paragraphs, forms, tables, and buttons.

Add styles to customize the appearance of the pages through the stylesheet (.css) file. This includes colors, fonts, margins, padding, and other properties related to the presentation of content.

Write the interactive behavior of the pages using JavaScript within the script file (.js). This will involve manipulating DOM elements, listening for events, and responding to them dynamically.


Code :

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Personal Finance Tracker</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>
<body>
    <div id="app">
        <h1>Personal Finance Tracker</h1>
        <div id="transactions">
            <h2>Transactions</h2>
            <table>
                <thead>
                    <tr>
                        <th>Date</th>
                        <th>Type</th>
                        <th>Amount</th>
                    </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <tr>
                        <td>2023-05-31</td>
                        <td>Income</td>
                        <td>$100</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>2023-05-30</td>
                        <td>Expense</td>
                        <td>$50</td>
                    </tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>
        </div>
        <div id="balance">
            <h2>Balance</h2>
            <p>$150</p>
        </div>
        <div id="add-transaction">
            <h2>Add Transaction</h2>
            <form action="#">
                <input type="date" name="date">
                <input type="radio" name="type" value="income"> Income
                <input type="radio" name="type" value="expense"> Expense
                <input type="number" name="amount">
                <button type="submit">Add Transaction</button>
            </form>
        </div>
    </div>
    <script src="app.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
